    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Book Cover</th>
            <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><img src="https://encrypted-tbn2.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSxQc9_zh01kG5GiNnifnPyDdvxmgNbWjCmj9H3GczvpCzq9a6p" width="100"></td>
            <td>Burmese Days is the first novel by English writer George Orwell, published in 1934. Set in British Burma during the waning days of empire, when Burma was ruled from Delhi as part of British India, the novel serves as "a portrait of the dark side of the British Raj."
</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><img src="https://encrypted-tbn3.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcS7Q_596Qtib5SxZnQN71z99UFAYnbscDYaG-F2TQOBqIemmCOK" alt="Book 2 Cover" width="100"></td>
